<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 13.5pt;">Welcome to the Engineers and Architects Association. We are pleased that you are interested in learning more about our union. EAA represents approximately 4,500 employees in the City of Los Angeles and is the longest standing City union. EAA has represented City employees continuously since it was established in 1894.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: Arial;">Our highly educated union sisters and brothers are employedÂ  inÂ  aÂ  wide variety of occupations in the administrative, professional, and technical fields and many are supervisors or managers. Typical occupations include accountants, planners,Â hygienists, IT professionals, management analysts, drafting technicians, and biologists. EAA members are employed in virtually every City department including Police, Fire, Airports, Public Works, and Harbor. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: Arial;">Our members work at hundreds of locations throughout Los Angeles, from San Pedro to the San Fernando Valley, from Boyle Heights to Bel-Air, and from Hollywood to Westwood. When citizens of Los Angeles require any service from the City government, EAA members are involved in providing that service. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: Arial;">Enjoy your visit to our website and visit frequently for news updates and messages from EAA Board of Governors. </span></p>
